Reasoning: The paper proposes a new method for object detection using R-CNN based detectors, which is a popular approach in computer vision (CV) research. The paper focuses on the classification and localization tasks, which are core components of object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method that combines fully connected and convolutional heads, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complementary nature of the classification tasks, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of bounding box regression, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the MS COCO dataset, which involves multimedia (MM) techniques. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
